|Playing a Possessed ''does'' require submitting an application.]]%0a> %0a> [[#Possessed]]%0a> !!Possessed%0a> *Dragons Tongue '_Inferno pg. 127-128_' - 1 restricted slot for non-Possessed characters%0a> *Vice 3 - 2 restricted slots%0a> *Purchasing extra 3 dot vestments at creation - 1 restricted slot%0a> *Infernal Will is equal to you Primary Vice%0a> *Per Inferno's Possessed creation guidelines, morality may be dropped to 3 at creation with storyteller approval. %0a> *Dropping from 7-6 for a Possessed is unrestricted. Every drop thereafter takes a restricted slot. %0a> %0a> [--%25color=#8450b5%25[[#wodstop| Back to top]]--]%0a> %0a> [[#Imm]]%0a> %25color=#8450b5%25[[GameRef.WoDSRules|Playing an Immortal ''does'' require submitting an application.]]%0a> %0a> [[#BB]]%0a> !!Blood Bathers%0a> *Blood Bathers should use the Mortal character sheet. %0a> *Starting Morality is required to be at 5 and Blood Bathers begin the chat with the 10 extra XP it gives. This does not take any restricted slots. %0a> *Players may use restricted slots to drop their morality further in exchange for XP, with ST approval. %0a> *Permanent WP begins at Res+Comp-1 and 8XP may be spent to buy the dot back at creation. %0a> %0a> [--%25color=#8450b5%25[[#wodstop| Back to top]]--]%0a> %0a> [[#BT]]%0a> !!Body Thief%0a> *Body Thieves should use the Thaumaturge character sheet.%0a> *Replace the free four dot Thaumaturgy merit with the appropriate free four dot society merit if you are a member in good standing (ie. purchasing a dot of Society Status) in the society.%0a> *Half priced merits must be calculated manually. You may go into negative general XP by an the amount of the difference. For example. If you spend 6XP for two dots on a discounted merit then you may take your general XP to -3. This should be detailed in the notes section of the sheet for easy reference by the storyteller.%0a> %0a> [[#Club]]%0a> 1.The Club%0a> *Emotional Urging (4) is free%0a> *Half Price Resources, Status, Retainer, 